#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:2
msgid "ctest_update"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:4
msgid "Perform the :ref:`CTest Update Step` as a :ref:`Dashboard Client`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:6
msgid ""
"ctest_update([SOURCE <source-dir>]\n"
"             [RETURN_VALUE <result-var>]\n"
"             [VERSION_ONLY]\n"
"             [VERSION_OVERRIDE <version>]\n"
"             [CAPTURE_CMAKE_ERROR <result-var>]\n"
"             [QUIET])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:15
msgid ""
"Update the source tree from version control and record results in ``Update."
"xml`` for submission with the :command:`ctest_submit` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:18
msgid "The options are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:20
msgid "``SOURCE <source-dir>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:21
msgid ""
"Specify the source directory.  If not given, the :variable:"
"`CTEST_SOURCE_DIRECTORY` variable is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:24
msgid "``RETURN_VALUE <result-var>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:25
msgid ""
"Store in the ``<result-var>`` variable the number of files updated or ``-1`` "
"on error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:28
msgid "``VERSION_ONLY``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:31
msgid ""
"Record the currently checked out revision without updating the source tree "
"to a different version.  This is equivalent to setting the :variable:"
"`CTEST_UPDATE_VERSION_ONLY` variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:35
msgid "``VERSION_OVERRIDE <version>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:38
msgid ""
"Report ``<version>`` as the current revision without querying or updating "
"the source tree.  This is equivalent to setting the :variable:"
"`CTEST_UPDATE_VERSION_OVERRIDE` variable, and supersedes ``VERSION_ONLY``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:43
msgid "``CAPTURE_CMAKE_ERROR <result-var>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:46
msgid ""
"Store in the ``<result-var>`` variable ``-1`` if there are any errors "
"running the command and prevent :manual:`ctest(1)` from returning non-zero "
"if an error occurs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:50
msgid "``QUIET``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:53
msgid ""
"Suppress any CTest-specific non-error messages that would have otherwise "
"been printed to the console.  CTest will still report the new revision of "
"the repository and any conflicting files that were found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/ctest_update.rst:58
msgid ""
"By default, the update follows the version control branch currently checked "
"out in the source directory.  The ``VERSION_ONLY`` and ``VERSION_OVERRIDE`` "
"options instead record revision information without changing the source "
"tree.  See the :ref:`CTest Update Step` documentation for information about "
"further variables that change the behavior of ``ctest_update()``."
msgstr ""
